<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Db_Table_Abstract has a getter method for $this-&gt;_rowClass.  However, it does not use it in it's own functions - it references $this-&gt;_rowClass directly.  This obviates their purpose, as far as I can see.</p>

<p>This means that developers cannot write custom logic to set $this-&gt;_rowClass.  For instance, in my use-case, I have a digitalAssets table which contains filesystem references to images, MP3s, etc.  It would be helpful if I could  override $this-&gt;getRowClass() to return different row classes for each of these types - imageAsset, mp3Asset, etc.</p>

    </div>
</div>

